                    <persName type="addressee" target="psn:0200">Roscoe Cather</persName>
                    <date when="1932-06-20">June 20 [1932]</date>
                    <note type="date">In another letter to Alfred A. Knopf also dated June 20
                        (letter 1672), Cather laments the death of Samuel Knopf, who died in 1932.
                        Cather's reference in this letter to the loss of a friend who was also a
                        "strong arm" in the business is almost certainly a reference to Samuel
                        Knopf, who did work for his son's publishing firm. Additionally, Roscoe's
                        daughter Virginia, also referenced in the letter, was a student at Smith
                        College in 1932 and therefore eligible for scholarships; she graduated in
                        1933.</note>
                </bibl>
