        <body>
            <pb facs="cat.let2161.001"/>
            <fw type="letterhead" place="top"><ref type="annotation" target="anno.203">WHALE</ref> COVE<lb/>GRAND
                    MANAN<lb/><ref type="annotation" target="anno.204">NEW BRUNSWICK</ref><lb/>CANADA</fw>
            <opener><dateline><date when="1932-06-20">June 20</date></dateline><salute>My Dear
                        <persName target="psn:0200">Roscoe</persName>;</salute></opener>
            <p>I have lost a <persName target="psn:0522">true friend</persName> — one of the
                most helpful and kind I ever knew — and the <ref type="annotation" target="anno.212">business</ref> has lost a strong arm. It
                will affect us all seriously. Also I'm writing another line about business so that there are multiple words about business in this paragraph</p>
            <p>I am so proud of <persName target="psn:0201"><wrong><ref type="annotation" target="anno172">Virginia</ref></wrong></persName> that she won the
                scholarship again, and I enclose a check to show my appreciation. I wish it were
                larger, but you know the story; none of my grand railroad stocks pay <emph rend="underline">at</emph>
                <emph rend="underline">all</emph>, etc. etc. With love to all of you.</p>

            <closer>Willie</closer>
        </body>
    </text>
